aVRepublicans will go to any length to divert attention away from the disaster that is Donald Trump.\u000a\u000aAnd they think they have found their perfect foil in Florida Congresswoman Debbie Wasserman Schultz over her handling of an information technology aide whom she kept on the payroll for months after he was banned from the House IT network.\u000a\u000aWasserman Schultz has committed no crime. None. Nip. Nada.\u000a\u000aBut Republicans are trying to turn this into something bigger than Watergate. They are doing this because there are three Democrats they really can\u2019t stand \u2014 Hillary Clinton, Nancy Pelosi, and Wasserman Schultz.\u000a\u000aAnd they are doing it to take attention away from how Trump is lying and messing up the country.\u000a\u000aSo you have Tim Canova, who is challenging Wasserman Schultz in next year\u2019s Democratic primary, saying \u201cmillions of Americans\u201d don\u2019t trust Wasserman Schultz to give straight answers.\u000a\u000aMillions? I assume Canova has talked to them all before making a statement like that.\u000a\u000aYou have U.S. Rep. Ron DeSantis, R-Ponte Vedra Beach, terming the events \u201cextremely odd\u201d on Fox News, which will go with any conspiracy theory that involves Democrats.\u000a\u000aEven Sarah Palin, the lightweight who is an expert on nothing, weighed in on Twitter, calling the situation \u201cJust unbelievable.\u201d\u000a\u000aAgain, Wasserman Schultz committed no crime. She said she didn\u2019t fire Imran Awan until July 25 \u2014 after he was arrested, and after all others he worked for in the House had fired him \u2014 because he may have been put under scrutiny because of his Muslim faith.\u000a\u000aRepublicans will try hard to to turn this into Watergate. Or maybe they\u2019ll hold countless hearings, like when they went after Hillary Clinton because of Benghazi.\u000a\u000aThe ACLU has said Wasserman Schultz appeared to have acted appropriately.\u000a\u000aBut Ronna Romney McDaniel, chairwoman of the Republican National Committee, couldn\u2019t stop criticizing Wasserman Schultz.\u000a\u000a\u201cWe have to get to the bottom of this,\u201d she said, \u201cand Debbie Wasserman Schultz has obstructed at every level on something that affects potentially our national security.\u201d\u000a\u000aBetter she should worry about obstruction coming from the White House.\u000a\u000aBut hey, why do that, when you can grill Debbie Wasserman Schultz?\u000a\u000aGary Stein can be reached at gstein@sunsentinel.com. On Twitter@SSEditorial.
